<HEADLINE> Argentine President Calls To Create a True Common Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Argentine president said, as he opened Friday in Buenos
Aires the Sixth Meeting of the Forum of the Leaders of Mercosur,
the importance of having solid and strong internal markets to face
the restrictions to commerce.
</P>
<P>
He said that "expanding our common market will make us stronger
to face the unbalances that globalization might cause."
</P>
<P>
He also called to unite to defend together the trade of primary
products from European restrictions, barriers and subsidies and to
demand the opening of the northern markets, referring to the
United States and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine president also called to surmount differences
within Mercosur, to create a strong association.
</P>
<P>
De la Rua also mentioned the possibility of having a common
currency for the regional organization.
</P>
<P>
He said that to achieve this goal, it is necessary to first
find the needed macroeconomic equilibrium between the member
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Sixth Meeting of the Forum of Mercosur Leaders is being
held Friday in the Argentine capital with the attendance of the
businessmen of the four countries of the bloc.
</P>
<P>
Some of the themes to be discussed by the work groups are
commercial aspects, strategies for Mercosur, education and culture,
and the institutionalization of matters related to the
implementation of the unique currency, macroeconomic policies, and
courts for the solution of controversies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
