<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Counties Call To Set a New Global Human Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 133 member countries of the G-77 are eager to promote
growth with equity, the eradication of poverty, the expansion of
productive employment and the promotion of social integration.
</P>
<P>
They are convinced of the need to crate a new spirit of
international cooperation based on the principle of achieving
shared benefits, but also based on common but different
responsibilities, between the developing and industrialized
countries.
</P>
<P>
The hope to develop collective solutions for the global
problems affecting the world today, calling for the creation of a
concrete mechanisms to guarantee full and effective participation
on an equal basis by the South in International decision -making.
</P>
<P>
The South counties ask to participate on an equal footing in
decisions which affect them most of all, in particular, economic
governance institutions must promote broad-based decision-making.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to promote a North-South dialogue based on the
spirit of partnership, mutual benefit and genuine interdependence
in order to have a more equitable global political economy, said
the document, 
</P>
</TEXT>
