<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sweden Welcomes Russian Duma's Ratification of START-II </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Sweden welcomes Russian State
Duma's ratification of the Russian-U.S. second-phase Strategic
Arms Reduction Treaty (START-II), said Swedish Foreign Secretary
Anna Lindh on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ratification of START-II is a step toward the nuclear
disarmament and brings hope to the start of a constructive
dialogue between Russia and the United States for the modification
of the treaty on nonproliferation of nuclear weapons, Lindh said.
</P>
<P>
She hopes that Russia could complete the process of the
ratification of the START-II as soon as possible and urges Russia
to take further steps to ratify the treaty on the prohibition of
nuclear test and to reduce by big margin the number of tactical
nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Lindh urges the United States to complete the
ratification of the START-II as soon as possible. She also hopes
that Russia and the United States can further reduce strategic and
tactical nuclear weapons during START-III.
</P>
<P>
Lindh said that Sweden's final objective is to have a nuclear-
free world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
