<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of today
's diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
 Reception Marks China-Indonesia Diplomatic Relations
</P>
<P>
The Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign
Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception this evening to mark the 50th
anniversary of the establishment of Sino-Indonesian diplomatic
relations.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, together with other senior Chinese and
Indonesian officials, attended the gathering.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said in his address that the
friendship between the two countries can be traced back for
decades. Indonesia is among the first countries which recognized
new China after its founding in 1949.
</P>
<P>
China Strongly Resents Tokyo Governor's Remarks: FM Spokesman
</P>
<P>
China has expressed its strong resentment over the "evil
remarks" of Shintaro Ishihara, governor of Tokyo, who claims that
China is Japan's biggest threat, China's Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Sun Yuxi said here.
</P>
<P>
"We express strong resentment over Shintaro Ishihara who once
again publicly made evil remarks against China and the Chinese
people," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
In the interview with the German media, Ishihara asserted that
China is Japan's biggest threat, and therefore, should be divided
into several small countries, and Japan should do its part to
promote this.
</P>
<P>
China Firmly Opposes Any Trip to Japan by Lee Teng-hui
</P>
<P>
China firmly opposes any trip to Japan by Lee Teng-hui of
Taiwan, and is paying close attention to some Japanese anti-China
forces' planned invitation to Lee, China's Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Sun Yuxi said here.
</P>
<P>
"We are paying close attention to the anti-China forces in
Japan who have actively plotted to invite Lee Teng-hui to visit
Japan," Sun said in response to a question concerning Japanese
right-wing scholar Nakajima Mineo's plan to invite Lee to attend a
forum in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stressed that it is well-known that Lee Teng-hui
is the general incarnation of "Taiwan independence," and his visit
to Japan in whatever form or capacity is opposed by the Chinese
side. 
</P>
</TEXT>
