<HEADLINE> Americans Remember Nanjing Massacre With Roses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The El Paso, Texas, Rose
Cultivators Association, headed by Dr. B. Merrell Frazer,
presented 160 roses to the Nanjing Massacre Memorial Hall today.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Frazer, a lawyer and historian, said at the presentation
ceremony that Americans should not forget two important dates in
history: December 7, 1941, when Japanese bombed Pearl Harbor; and
the Nanjing Massacre of 1937.
</P>
<P>
Texas is a well-known rose cultivation base in the United
States, and giving roses to the memorial hall demonstrates the
American people's wish for everlasting world peace, Dr. Frazer
said.
</P>
<P>
In December 1937, the Japanese army massacred 300,000 Chinese
civilians and soldiers in Nanjing, then the capital of the
Kuomintang regime.  
</P>
</TEXT>
