<HEADLINE> START-II Approval "Historical Mistake": Russian Communist Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Russian Communis Party leader
Gennady Zyuganov described the ratification of START-II by the
State Duma, lower house of parliament, as "a historical mistake"
and "another defeat for Russia."
</P>
<P>
"Our opponents in the Duma have military discipline," he said,
explaining the result of the voting.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the results of the State Duma voting, Zyuganov
said he is sure that the electorate will ask for explanations from
the deputies they chose.
</P>
<P>
Now the Communist leader is said to expect his political
opponents "to sell out the land" and take other decisions "equally
ruinous for the country."
</P>
<P>
At Friday's session, almost all Duma factions, except
Communists, Agrarians, voted for START-II ratification
</P>
<P>
The State Duma supported the pact ratification 288-131 with
four abstentions. The necessary majority was 226.
</P>
<P>
As many as 82 of all 88 Communist deputies, including Zyuganov,
voted against. Duma Speaker Gennady Seleznyov, another Communist
leader, did not vote. Only two Communists supported ratification.
</P>
