<HEADLINE> China Hosts International Young Designers Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth Brother Cup China
International Young Designers Contest held its final round of
competition in Beijing today, and local designer Zou You placed
first with his clothing collection series called "Half and Half."
</P>
<P>
This contest, which has been held annually since 1993, is a
major part of the eighth session of the China International
Clothing and Accessories Fair (CHIC 2000), one of the largest of
its kind in the world.
</P>
<P>
There are 1,061 contestants this year, 866 of whom are from
China, with the others from 28 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
After the preliminary round, 36 clothing collections from 19
countries and regions were selected for the finals.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the contest this year is "Prospects for the 21
Century." World-renowned fashion critics such as Annette Goldstein
from France and Junko Ouchi from Japan, as well as fashion
authorities from the United States, Norway, Italy, and China acted
as judges for the competition.
</P>
<P>
The competition is exclusively sponsored by Japan's Brother
Industries Ltd., one of the world's largest producers of
electronic printers and sewing machines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
