<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Network Solution Debuts on Chinese Campuses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A new network solution that is
expected to improve information exchange on campuses made its
trial run in three Chinese universities today.
</P>
<P>
CampusAge, created by a group of Qinghua University students,
was designed to remedy the inconvenience and limited flow of
information on campuses by providing students with on-line
services and news releases about their schools.
</P>
<P>
Using 6.6 million yuan in funding, the Qinghua students put
their studies on hold in January to start a new Internet website,
FanSo.com.
</P>
<P>
The young entrepreneurs believe that revealing campus culture
to the outside will help the public know more about students'
needs, and will promote the development of e-commerce on campus.
</P>
<P>
A report from the China Internet Network Information Center
said that China had 10 million netizens by March this year; 21
percent are college students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
