<HEADLINE> Reception Marks China-Indonesia Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception
this evening to mark the 50th anniversary of the establishment of
Sino-Indonesian diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, together with other senior Chinese and
Indonesian officials, attended the gathering.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said in his address that the
friendship between the two countries can be traced back for
decades. Indonesia is among the first countries which recognized
new China after its founding in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The two countries supported each other in national construction
and international affairs. After half a century of turbulence, the
two countries scored prompt recovery and development in bilateral
cooperation in political, economic, cultural, scientific and
technological fields after resuming their diplomatic ties a decade
ago.
</P>
<P>
As both are developing countries, there is still potential to
tap in bilateral cooperation, for such cooperation is in the best
interests of the two peoples and is conducive to stability and
prosperity in the Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Qi also had high praise for the efforts made by Indonesian
President Abdurrahman Wahid and the Indonesian government to
develop ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian ambassador to China Kuntara also spoke well of the
Indonesia-China relationship after reviewing the bilateral
relations during the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral relations showed substantial progress
in the past decade. He believed that under the leadership of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid, bilateral relations in political, economic, social and
cultural areas will tighten, bringing benefits for both nations.
</P>
</TEXT>
