<HEADLINE> Online Venture Capital Industry Emerges in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Internet will become the tool
of choice for developing China's venture capital industry which
has been growing very fast these days, experts said here today.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar covering issues of the newly-emerged online
venture capital industry held today, overseas investors and
representatives from domestic investment groups agreed that the
Internet will have profound influence on the traditional venture
capital industry and technology innovation in China.
</P>
<P>
The Internet has proved a very efficient medium for linking
buyers and sellers, and also can be used in the process of
obtaining start-up funding for companies.
</P>
<P>
China's venture capital industry started in 1985, and the
country's first website on venture capital opened in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Yan Zhubing, president of the Beijing City Commercial Bank (
BCCB), said at the seminar that venture capital has already
stimulated China's technology innovation, and is acknowledged by
most investors.
</P>
<P>
Seminar participants agreed that the online venture capital
industry has found a new base for expansion since the Internet is
flourishing in China.
</P>
<P>
Today's seminar was co-held by the BCCB, a management college
of Canada, China's Young Entrepreneur Association and the China
Venture Capital Association. 
</P>
