<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- German brewer Hans Stecker was
awarded "Golden Embroidered Ball" by the government of the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region here today for his contributions to a
local brewery.
</P>
<P>
According to the Zhuang ethnic tradition, young women used to
be given a fist-sized embroidered ball by their boyfriends as a
symbol of love, and these days it represents friendship.
</P>
<P>
The 72-year-old beer brewing expert came to Liuzhou City of
Guangxi last year to spread brewing techniques and offer materials
used by his family, which helped the Yufeng Beer Plant to
significantly improve product quality.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter this year, the brewery sold 800 tons of
the new beer, which has been widely praised for its flavor.
</P>
<P>
The Golden Embroidered Ball Prize was created in 1994 for
foreign experts working in Guangxi. Seventy-one have been
presented so far.  
