<HEADLINE> Mine Blast Kills 3, Wounds 12 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- At least three Sri Lankan
military personnel including one officer were killed and 12
soldiers wounded on Friday when a vehicle carrying them got caught
in a rebel pressure mine explosion in northern Wanni region.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Defense said in a statement that the troops
were returning from a search operation at Awarantalawa, some 250
kilometers north of Colombo, where they had gone to counterattack
the rebels who had attacked a home guard point there Friday
morning.
</P>
<P>
It said rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
killed one home guard in the attack.
</P>
