attack on the home guard point as a bait to draw the army into the
mine trap.
</P>
<P>
The injured soldiers were evacuated to a nearby Vavuniya
hospital for treatment, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ministry of Defense said Friday that at least 15
LTTE rebels had been killed in the latest clashes in the
northernmost Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, fighting for a separate homeland for minority
Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983, have intensified
their offensives in recent weeks in a bid to take back their
former stronghold of Jaffna, which they lost in 1996. 
