<HEADLINE> China to Tackle Sandstorms to Protect Beijing's Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China has worked out a plan to
tackle desertification and pollution in the northern part of the
country, especially in areas around the capital, to make a clean
Beijing, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Guo Peizhang, from the State Development Planning Commission (
SDPC), said today that the duststorms and contaminated water in
regions north of Beijing are posing an enormous threat to the
capital's environment.
</P>
<P>
The SDPC initiated a plan to tackle the issue a year ago,
calling government departments in Beijing and neighboring Hebei
Province to improve the environment in periphery areas of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The plan provides concrete measures to protect the environment
such as tightening regulations and supervision over the management
of resources, return of farmland to grass and forests and
application of eco-technologies.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has been bit by severe sandstorms this spring showering
the city with dust and sand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
