<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Army Reaches World Standards In Clearing Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese army has reached
international levels in clearing mines, according to army sources.
</P>
<P>
This was confirmed by experts from the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA) and the United Nations who recently
inspected and studied the results of two rounds of large-scale
mine clearing operations carried out by the Chinese army along the
Sino-Vietnamese border during 1992-99.
</P>
<P>
PLA troops have developed numerous methods and techniques to
clear mines. They have cleared more than 600 square meters of
landmines per day. So far, there have been no reports of
casualties.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000-strong mine-clearing PLA troops suffered much less
casualties during the maneuver compared with their foreign
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, China and the United Nations held an international
training course for trainees from countries including Cambodia.
</P>
</TEXT>
