<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Population to Increase by 10 Million Per Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China's total population will
increase by more than 10 million each year in the next ten years,
reaching a peak of 1.6 billion by the middle of the 21st century,
officials with the State Family Planning Commission said here
today.
</P>
<P>
It won't be easy for China to maintain the slow growth rate of
its vast population, which now stands at 12.5 billion, because it
hit the current growth level in just 30 years, far less than the
100 years such growth would require in developed countries, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the birth control policy must continue to be
enforced to prevent the instability that could emerge because of a
massive population.
</P>
<P>
Poor economic conditions in many areas of the country are
another major obstacle facing the success of the birth control
policy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Experts here believe China's population will gradually shrink
after the mid-21st century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
