<HEADLINE> Southeast China University Merges Three Colleges in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- In the current national drive to
merge colleges and universities, prestigious Southeast China
University in Nanjing, capital of East China's Jiangsu Province,
annexed three local colleges today.
</P>
<P>
Southeast China University, founded in 1902, is one of the
first institutions of higher learning in China. It was known as
National Central University in the first half of this century.
</P>
<P>
The university, famous for its engineering program, has merged
the Nanjing Railway Medical College, Nanjing Transportation
College and Nanjing Geological School to further strengthen its
advantage in engineering and science studies.
</P>
<P>
Gu Guanqun, a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering,
will remain as president of the new Southeast China University.
</P>
