<HEADLINE> Blizzard Hits Ethnic Prefecture in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Severe snow storms have hit a
number of counties in the Ganzi Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture in
southwest China's Sichuan Province over the past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The county of Litang has been hit by heavy snowstorms since
last November, and in early April, new snowfalls have brought an
average of one-meter deep snow to the county, resulting in the
death of 50,000 head of livestock and over 80 herdsmen lost
contacts.
</P>
<P>
The county is at an elevation of 3,600 meters, and its economy
is mainly based on animal husbandry, according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
The Sichuan Provincial People's Government has paid close
attention to the situation from the very beginning, sending many
officials to the spot to carry out round-the-clock relief work.
</P>
<P>
To date, Litang County has been provided with 50,000 kg of
foodstuff and an abundant medical supplies and firewood.
</P>
<P>
The heavy snowfalls are expected to end in the area in the next
few days, according to meteorologists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
