<HEADLINE> Philippines to Lure Investment in IT Projects: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will be offering a
package of incentives for investments in information technology (
IT) projects, Philippine News Agency (PNA) said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Trade Secretary Mar Roxas was quoted as saying in a roundtable
discussion here with business executives that this will be
realized once a new draft of the proposed changes to the Omnibus
Investments Code is approved by Congress.
</P>
<P>
The bill pending in Congress would lower the minimum qualifying
amount from 1 billion U.S. dollars to 500 million dollars for
incentives such as a 12-year tax holiday and a five-year net
operating loss, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Roxas said that if the bill is approved, the Philippines will
be at least on an equal competitive footing with its neighbors
during presentations for potential investors.
</P>
<P>
The government will spare no effort in pushing ahead the
passage of the bills that are pending in Congress but in urgent
need to boost the IT industry including electronic commerce (E-
Commerce) in the country, he said. 
</P>
