<HEADLINE> S. Africa Urges UK to Help Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki has called on Britain to honor the 1979 Lancaster
House agreement with Zimbabwe and to help the country's
government resolve the land question, South African Broadcasting
Corporation radio news reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing journalists at the G77 summit meeting in Havana,
Cuba, Mbeki said the land issue was an old problem that was
central to the liberation struggle in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
He said he has raised the matter with British Prime Minister
Tony Blair and urged the British and American governments to
carry out their undertakings to make funds available to deal with
the land issue in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki expressed the hope that Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe and British Foreign Secretary Robin Cooke will continue
their dialogue until a solution has been found. 
</P>
