<HEADLINE> Russian State Duma Ratifies START-II Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Russian State Duma ratified the
1993 second-phase Russian-U.S. Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (
START-II) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The vote was 288 in favor with 131 against and four abstentions.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-seven deputies were not present in the 450-seat Duma
during the voting.
</P>
<P>
Russian President-elect Vladimir Putin attended the closed-door
session, strongly urging deputies to approve the treaty, under
which the United States and Russia agree to reduce the number of
nuclear warheads from 6,000 to no more than 3,500 by 2007.
</P>
<P>
Putin said: "We don't need another arms race" which would be
worse than the Cold War and Russia could not afford for it.
</P>
<P>
Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev, Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov and Russian Security Council Secretary Sergey Ivanov were
also present at Friday's debate on the issue. 
