<HEADLINE> South Korean Chip Exports Up 17 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 14 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's exports of all
semiconductor chips hit 3.54 billion U.S. dollars during the first
two months this year, up 17.2 percent from the same period last
year, the Korea Semiconductor Industry Association said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The export of DRAM chips amounted to 1.48 billion dollars in
the period, up 65.9 percent from the same time last year.
</P>
<P>
The export of memory chips totaled 1.72 billion dollars, up 52.
1 percent while non-memory chips reached 225 million dollars, up
77.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the export of other chips decreased 10.6 percent to 1.
55 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The association said this year's target for chip exports of 23.
5 billion dollars will not be difficult to reach as the price of
64 Mega DRAM chips in the world market has been on rise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
