<HEADLINE> 87th China Export Commodity Fair Set to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The 87th China Export Commodity
Fair will open tomorrow in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, said a foreign trade official here today.
</P>
<P>
Hu Chusheng, spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), said in a news release that the
fair is a biannual event popularly considered a weathervane for
China's foreign trade. Since the first such fair in 1957, it has
attracted some 3,000 domestic and overseas enterprises annually
which display over 100,000 kinds of commodities.
</P>
<P>
The province has built an exposition center for the fair
covering a total of 170,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that in the first quarter this year,
China exported 98.21 billion U.S. dollars worth of commodities, up
40 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the January-March period, China approved the establishment
of 4,316 overseas-funded enterprises, up 22.75 percent over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The fair, sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation, is expected to account for one-fourth of
the country's total export trade volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
