<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Allows On-Line Stock Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The China Securities Regulatory
Commission( CSRC) the industry's watchdog, has enacted a new
regulation which allows authorized securities firms to trade
stocks on-line.
</P>
<P>
Unauthorized securities firms and other institutions will not
be able to engage in this activity, and cooperation with such
entities for on-line stock trading is also prohibited, according
to today's China Securities.
</P>
<P>
Securities firms applying for authorization must follow strict
guidelines and go through special procedures.
</P>
<P>
Those authorized are also required to inform on-line investors
of all possible risks in written form.
</P>
<P>
Any violation of the regulation will lead to fines, suspension
of business, or even revocation of trading licenses, the CSRC said.
</P>
<P>
China now has 10 million Internet users and more than 40
million stock investors, and it is estimated that there are now
100,000 investors nationwide trading in stocks on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that with improving Internet safety, higher
browsing speeds, and greater Internet coverage and lower costs, on-
line stock trading will develop rapidly in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
