<HEADLINE> China Strongly Resents Tokyo Governor's Remarks: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China has expressed its strong
resentment over the "evil remarks" of Shintaro Ishihara, governor
of Tokyo, who claims that China is Japan's biggest threat, China's
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We express strong resentment over Shintaro Ishihara who once
again publicly made evil remarks against China and the Chinese
people," Sun said in response to a question concerning the Tokyo
governor's recent statement to the German media.
</P>
<P>
In the interview with the German media, Ishihara asserted that
China is Japan's biggest threat, and therefore, should be divided
into several small countries, and Japan should do its part to
promote this.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman said Ishihara's remarks
are in direct line with the vicious intentions of Japanese
militarists who once attempted to divide and annex China. this
once again reveals Ishihara as an element of the remnants of
militarism.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of New China and especially since China
began its reform and opening up drive, the country's economy has
been developing rapidly and the Chinese people's lives have been
constantly improved.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proved, and will continue to prove, that no force
whatsoever can stop the development of China," Sun stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Ishihara's wild remarks are but the dream of a slow-witted man
and will never come true," Sun said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
