<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Further Lower on Wall Street Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices closed
sharply lower Friday, effected by overnight falls on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications, media and technology-related issues dragged
the key Hang Seng Index (HSI) down 209.80 points, or 1.28 percent,
to close at 16,142.76, after falling 1.9 percent in morning trade.
</P>
<P>
Turnover sank to 11.617 billion HK dollars (1.489 billion U.S.
dollars), down from Thursday's 15.251 billion HK dollars (1.955
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of HSI, Finance, Utilities and
Properties rose slightly, by 0.14 percent, 0.72 percent and 0.07
percent, respectively, while Commerce and Industry registered a
loss of 2.50 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises went up 5.67 percent while Hang
Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index down 0.96 percent.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip Hang Seng index went downward from Monday's 16,
850.74 to Friday's 16,142.76, as sentiment dampened by Wall Street
's continued declines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
