<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inland Universities of China Hold Exhibition in Macao SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A three-day exhibition, jointly
organized by 23 universities in the inland areas of China, opened
here Friday as part of the effort to recruit more students from
the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is aimed at enabling Macao students to know more
about the universities and relevant courses, so that they have
more options in acquiring higher education, said Ma Qinrong, head
of a delegation comprising representatives from the universities.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several days, the representatives have visited
local high schools and given lectures to publicize their
universities and explain recruiting formalities.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is the first of its kind since Macao's return to
the motherland in last December. Similar exhibitions have been
conducted since 1993.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, nearly 1,000 students from Macao went to study in
universities in the inland areas of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
