<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Encyclopedia of Macao Accessible on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Encyclopedia of Macao, a
comprehensive reference book published last year, has been made
available on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Internet surfers just type in the website of www.unesco.org.mo
and a window featuring the encyclopedia pops up. Readers can
browse through it or search for any single entry.
</P>
<P>
Published by the Macao Foundation, the encyclopedia in the
complex form of Chinese contains 1.7 million Chinese characters
and nearly 1,000 color and white-and-black pictures. Total entries
add up to 2,989.
</P>
<P>
The encyclopedia cover every aspects of Macao, such as its
politics, legal system, economy, history, geography, cultural
affairs, education, religion, folk customs, and celebrities.
</P>
</TEXT>
