<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday on persistent selling
following the depression of Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 2.64
points to 931.21, the all-share Emas Index fell 0.71 of a point to
243.44, the Industrial Index shed 6.08 points to 1,596.12 and the
Second Board Index dropped 0.29 of a point to 276.78.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 349 to 329 while 183 counters were
unchanged and 101 untraded.
</P>
