<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Stresses Importance of Financial Affairs: Magazine (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Ample financial resources and
correct fiscal policies are of vital importance to a nation's
development, prosperity and stability, President Jiang Zemin
recently told senior government officials in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks when delivering a speech on January 19
at a special symposium on finance and taxation attended by
government officials at the provincial level.
</P>
<P>
"Seeking Truth," a theoretic periodical of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), will publish the
speech in its April 17 edition.
</P>
<P>
In his talk, the president stressed the importance of financial
work in the country's overall development, saying that China needs
powerful state finance to promote the building of socialism with
Chinese characteristics, improve the living standards of the
Chinese people, and maintain social stability, economic growth,
and national security.
</P>
<P>
The basic criteria for judging whether or not a country's
financial work is well done should include: if it contributes to
the development of a socialist market economy and the
consolidation of socialist system, if it helps protect and promote
the basic interests of the people, and if it maintains the
country's unity, security, solidarity between different ethnic
groups, and social stability, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said the government should set the general goals and
direction of financial work in accordance with the political
situation and China's economic and social development, and make it
serve the country's reform, development, and stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Stresses Importance of Financial Affairs: Magazine (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Financial departments should first meet the basic needs of the
people before they go further and invest in social and economic
development, Jiang stressed. He added that it is "ridiculous and
foolish" for some officials to divert financial funds earmarked
for improvement of the people's living conditions to construction
of projects planned for "demonstrating achievements of officials".
</P>
<P>
Financial work should follow the principle of balancing
revenues and expenditures, building the country through diligence
and thrift, and launching projects according to the state's
financial capabilities, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government should cut down redundant personnel in local and
grass-roots government departments so that state finances no
longer have to support so many people, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that both the share of the state financial revenue in
the gross domestic product (GDP) and that of the central
government in the national financial revenue should be raised, as
this will enable the state to make unified plans for central and
local budgets, and allocate more financial resources to priorities.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the government should improve and strengthen
tax collection methods and management, deepen the reform in this
regard, tighten supervision, severely deal with all acts of tax
evasion and tax fraud, and punish those who use violence to avoid
paying taxes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
