<HEADLINE> hke041436--Malaysia to Buy Armored Personnel Carriers from Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will buy 211
armored personnel carriers (APCs) from Turkey for its army,
Defense Minister Najib Tun Razak said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian government is in the final stage of negotiations
with the supplier, FMC Nurol of Turkey, he told reporters after
officiating the closing of the four-day Defense Services Asia 2000
exhibition and conference (DSA 2000) here.
</P>
<P>
Without mentioning the cost of the deal which was expected to
be
finalized in the near future, Najib said the first few units would
be built in Turkey with the rest locally by Malaysia's DRB-Hicom
Defense Technologies (Deftech).
</P>
<P>
He said any outside purchase of military hardware must benefit
Malaysia in terms of transfer of technology, use of local
materials and joint production.
</P>
<P>
The DSA 2000 attracted some 420 companies from 39 countries and
regions to showcase their state-of-the-art technologies and
military hardware. 
</P>
