<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lower in Tokyo
Friday, dragged down by weakness in New York share prices, with
the benchmark Nikkei index ending below 20,500 for the first time
in five trading days.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 91.74 points, or 0.45
percent, from Thursday's close to end at 20,434.68.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 10.32 points, or 0.62 percent, to 1,
653.70.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 683.44 million
shares from Thursday's 717.40 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's fall on Wall Street weighed on export-oriented high-
tech issues in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Issues in several sectors related to domestic demand faced
profit-taking following their recent gains, traders said, citing
the steel, chemical and real estate sectors.
</P>
<P>
Brokerage houses, banks and rubber makers also saw declines,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outnumbered
gainers 828 to 422, with 142 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
