Guangdong Province. Amway spent 120 million U.S. dollars to build
a plant in Guangzhou Economic Development Zone, which has become
Amway's largest overseas production center.
</P>
<P>
Amway built direct outlets in China in 1999, increasing its
annual sales to 850 million yuan (102 million U.S. dollars) from
less than 10 million yuan (1.2 million U.S. dollars) in 1988.
