<HEADLINE> Eximbank Provides Soft Loan to Jamaican Water-Supply Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The China Export and Import Bank
(Eximbank) and the Jamaican government signed an agreement here
today to support Jamaica's purchasing of tap water equipment with
soft loans.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the 100-million-yuan (about 13
million US dollars) soft loans will be used to purchase China-made
equipment for a Jamaican water-supply project.
</P>
<P>
China and Jamaica are both developing countries. Bilateral
relations have been developing very smoothly. Today's agreement
has been signed in accordance with a framework agreement concluded
between the two sides in October, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Eximbank has granted soft loans to 63 projects in 31 countries,
involving a total of 4.09 billion yuan. This is the first time
China has provided soft loans to Jamaica.
</P>
