<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhibition on China in 20th Century Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on China in the 20
th century, entitled "Vicissitudes of the Chinese Nation Over The
Past 100 Years", opened today at the Museum of the Chinese
Revolution in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits include over 150 relics and over 280 pictures
depicting the life of the Chinese people and great changes in the
country in the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
The Exhibition is divided into four parts: China's struggles
against foreign invaders and the founding of the Republic of China,
the armed revolution led by the Communist Party of China, the
founding of the People's Republic of China, and reforms since the
late seventies and early eighties.
</P>
<P>
Present at today's opening ceremony were Wang Guangying, a vice
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), three vice chairmen of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference Chen
Junsheng, Jing Shuping and Wang Wenyuan, and Rong Gaotang, vice
president of the Soong Ching Ling Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
