<HEADLINE> Australian Defense Force Ensign Becomes Official Flag </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The defense force ensign has
become an official Australian flag, Prime Minister John Howard
announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ensign was created in 1969 to identify military formations.
</P>
<P>
Its use has grown since then, but until now it has not been
recognized as an official flag of Australia.
</P>
<P>
Howard said in a statement that the ensigns of the Royal
Australian Navy and Royal Australian Air Force will continue in
use and represent their respective services.
</P>
<P>
"The role of the Australian Army as protector of the Australian
national flag continues unchanged," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The proclamation does not alter the pre-eminent status of the
Australian national flag," he added. 
</P>
