<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Kills 15 Rebels in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 Tamil Tiger rebels
had been killed in the latest clashes in their separatist war
against Sri Lanka's government troops, a military spokesman said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Col. R.P. Witana said troops on Thursday sniped and
killed eight rebels of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) at
Veddhakadu East in the northernmost Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Jaffna peninsula has seen bloody battles for three weeks as
LTTE rebels are trying to retake their former stronghold, which
they lost in 1996. Hundreds of rebels and soldiers have been
killed or wounded in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
Troops attacked a rebel bunker with rocket propelled grenades
and machine guns at Kattiaratan in Jaffna, killing four rebels,
said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said troops confronted a group of rebels at Thanankilappu in
Jaffna, killing three LTTE rebels and injuring three others.
</P>
<P>
However, rebels continued to fire mortars at troops manning
defenses at Veddhakadu, Ayanankai, Kattiaratan and Nagar Kovil.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said one soldier was killed and 33 were injured
due to rebel mortars.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, who have been fighting for a separate homeland
for minority Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983, have
vowed to take back Jaffna, which might help the LTTE negotiate
from a position of strength if and when peace talks with the
government begin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
