<HEADLINE> Vietnam Licenses First Two Stock Companies in Ho Chi Minh City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's State Securities
Commission has licensed the first two stock companies in Ho Chi
Minh City, the local press reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The stock companies, also the first in southern Vietnam, are
the First Share Holder Stock Company and the Sai Gon Share Holder
Stock Company with statutory capitals of 43 billion Vietnamese
dong (over 3 million U.S. dollars) and 6 billion Vietnamese dong (
429,000 U.S. dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
The First Share Holder Stock Company will become involved in
brokering, business, new issue guarantees, investment management
and consultancy.
</P>
<P>
The Sai Gon Share Holder Stock Company is allowed to involve
itself in brokering and investment consultancy only.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam will establish its first stock exchange center which is
scheduled to begin operating in July this year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam now has four stock companies. The other two are in
northern Vietnam, which are the Bao Viet Stock Company and the
Investment and Stock Co. Ltd. 
</P>
