<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Shows Ascending Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus stock market's all-share
index registered weekly gains of 5.3 percent as it closed on
Wednesday at 530.67 points, 26.61 points up compared with last
week, a weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, made by Cyprus' Financial Weekly newspaper, said the
index reached a high for the month of 543.57 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
All sectors without exception posted healthy gains. Total
advancers led decliners by 74 to 35 issues. 36 issues registered no
change.
</P>
<P>
The tourism sector led the advances with an overall weekly gain
of 23.67 percent compared with the insurance sector, which ended
with smaller gains of 4.78 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total volume for the week was particularly impressive as
they reached 171.1 million Cyprus pounds (290.9 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The average daily volume reached 34.2 million pounds (58.1
million dollars) up by 13.7 million pounds (23.3 million dollars)
or 66.8 percent compared with last week. 
