<HEADLINE> IBF Asks Indonesia to Include Mia Audina on Olympic Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Badminton Association of
Indonesia (PBSI) said that the International Badminton Federation
(IBF) requested Indonesia include Mia Audina, now world ranked 11,
in its Olympic contingent.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Mia, former Indonesian badminton star, left for
the Netherlands in July last year to reside with her Dutch-
Surinamese husband.
</P>
<P>
PBSI secretary-general Leo Chandra Wiranata said the IBF's
letter asked Indonesia to include Mia on the national team if the
International Olympic Committee turned down the request of the
Badminton Association of the Netherlands to allow her to represent
the country in the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The letter was signed by the federation's official in charge of
international championships and tournament open badminton rankings
Vanessa Freeman.
</P>
<P>
"I have to consult with PBSI chairman Subagyo Hadisiswoyo about
this matter. The decision is in his hands. I will give him some
aspects to consider. The most important thing is we must have a
personal letter from Mia assuring us that she will play for
Indonesia," he was quoted by the Jakarta Post Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
"I don't want something bad to happen during or after the
Olympics. We can't directly answer 'yes' or 'no' to the request,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Wiranata said PBSI would announce the decision by next week.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for Olympic badminton qualification is April 30.
The IBF is scheduled to announce the list of shuttlers for the
Games on May 1.
</P>
<P>
Wiranata said the IBF sent a letter last month asking PBSI to
support the Dutch bid to include Mia on its team for the Olympics
in Sydney in September.
</P>
<P>
"We didn't give any response to the call. In principal, we
leave the matter to the IBF rule saying that a player can
represent a new country in a multisports event if he or she has
resided in the country for one year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
