<HEADLINE> China: Top of the Week (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
the most important news Xinhua released over the past week from
April 7 to April 13.

April 7
</P>
<P>
-- Xu Guanhua, vice-minister of science and technology, said
that China will focus on developing advanced nuclear reactors with
its own intellectual property rights rather than merely relying on
foreign technologies.
</P>
<P>
-- Experts from China and the United States opened a seminar on
psychopathy and its influence on people.
</P>
<P>
-- Xinhua News Agency issued a commentator's article strongly
refuting Annette Lu's statements advocating "Taiwan independence"
when she was interviewed by a Hong Kong cable TV station on April
2.
</P>
<P>
-- China is planning to carry out the Sunshine Program in
housing construction. The program will spend 150 million US
dollars in the application of solar energy in construction,
particular in housing building.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Shi Guangsheng and visiting U.S. Commerce Secretary William M.
Daley issued a joint statement in the wake of the conclusion of
the 13th Session of the China-U.S. Joint Commission on Commerce
and Trade.
</P>
<P>
-- China urged the United States and Britain to cancel the "no-
fly" zone in Iraq and stop military actions against the country.
</P>
<P>
-- Many regions of the world are unlikely to reach this year's
poverty reduction target as set by the Social Summit of 1995, said
a United Nations Development Program (UNDP) report on world
poverty.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese Ministry of Agriculture will send a large
delegation to the International Agro-Foodtech Exposition to be
held in Beijing from April 11 to 14 to trade high-tech products
and attract foreign investment, a ministry official said.

April 8
</P>
<P>
-- China and Russia will enhance shipping cooperation on the
rivers on their borders, according to the 42nd regular meeting of
the Sino-Russian Joint Commission on Border River Shipping held
here.

April 9
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong of the Republic of Singapore
arrived here for an 11-day official visit to China at the
invitation of Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
-- A seminar for provincial and ministerial level officials on
international economy and trade was concluded here at the Party
School of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee.

April 10
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said here during talks with his
Singaporean counterpart Goh Chok Tong that China will never allow
Taiwan to separate from the motherland.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese government is promoting fiscal transfer as a
major financial support to accelerate development of the enormous
western territory. It will become the major channel for
facilitating development of west China, as the short-term pro-
active fiscal policy is going to be phased out, said Vice-Minister
of Finance Jin Liqun here.
</P>
<P>
-- China has developed the satellite perigee kick motor, known
as EPKM, entirely relying on its own efforts, according to a
spokesman of China Great Wall Industry Corporation.
</P>
<P>
-- China can play a much-needed, bigger role in the Mideast
peace process, Sadi Jaber, charge d'affaires of the Palestinian
embassy in Beijing, said.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese Government strongly demands that the U.S.
Government conduct a comprehensive and thorough investigation into
its bombing of the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia, bring the
perpetrators to justice and give the Chinese Government and people
a satisfactory explanation, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao
said here.
</P>
<P>
-- China expressed its welcome and support to the agreement
reached by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and
the Republic of Korea (ROK) that DPRK leader Kim Jong Il and ROK
president Kim Dae-jung will hold a summit in Pyongyang in mid-June.
</P>
<P>
-- China will promote mechanized paddy production nationwide as
it is crucial for modernizing the country's agriculture, Vice-
Minister of Agriculture Zhang Baowen said here.
</P>
</TEXT>
