<HEADLINE> South African Ambassador Confident of Sino-South African Ties (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Chris Dlamini, the first
Ambassador of South Africa to China, has expressed his full
confidence in the prospects of Sino-South African relations.
</P>
<P>
The fast-growing relationship between the two countries since
the establishment of their diplomatic relations two years ago
indicates that bilateral ties "is not just another" because of its
own fundamentals and connection between the leadership of both
countries and their peoples, said the ambassador in a recent
interview with Xinhua Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In his opinion, solid relations between China and South Africa
should be underpinned by strong economic and trade relations. He
said bilateral trade has been growing remarkably in recent years,
and now they need to focus more on direct investment, and
encourage their businesses to have more collaboration in the years
ahead.
</P>
<P>
Two-way trade between the two countries has grown from 14
million U.S. dollars in 1992 to over 1.6 billion U.S. dollars in
1998, according to Chinese statistics.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
