<HEADLINE> South African Ambassador Confident of Sino-South African Ties (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has been a friend and comrade of South Africa for a long
time, and has now accumulated resources, experience and technology
to assist developing countries, especially South Africa, to
promote its sustainable economic development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Chairman Li Peng of China's National People's
Congress Standing Committee and state vice-president Hu Jintao
visited South Africa in the past two years, and South African vice-
president and parliament leaders and former South African
President Nelson Mandela also visited China.
</P>
<P>
"President Jiang Zemin's impending state visit to South Africa
will be a culmination of the work that the people of the two
countries have been doing since the establishment of diplomatic
relations," Dlamini said.
</P>
<P>
Dlamini arrived in Beijing in April of 1997 to serve as the
director of the Beijing-based South African Center for Chinese
Studies, and then as the South African ambassador to China
beginning on January 1, 1998, when the two countries established
diplomatic ties.
</P>
</TEXT>
