<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rainy Weather Forecast for Parts of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Most of southern China and a
portion of northern China are expected to see rain over the next
two days, China's Central Meteorological Observatory said today.
</P>
<P>
The observatory said rainfall ranging from 5 to 20 mm are
forecast for today and tomorrow in most areas of southern China
and along the Yangtze River Basin, including the Hanshui River
Basin, the areas between the Yangtze and Huaihe rivers, south
China, east part of Guizhou Province and the areas between the
Yangtze River and the Nanling Mountains.
</P>
<P>
For some of the regions, the rainfalls are expected to be 30 to
50 mm, and 80 to 100 mm for isolated areas with occasional strong
winds and thunder storms.
</P>
<P>
Southwestern China is expected to have rainfalls of 5 to 15 mm
during April 16 to 17.
</P>
<P>
Strong breeze to fresh gale is forecast for middle and southern
parts of the Yellow Sea, the East China Sea and the Taiwan Strait
today and tomorrow, while fresh breeze to moderate gale is
expected for the Bohai Sea, the northern Yellow Sea and middle and
northern parts of the South China Sea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
