<HEADLINE> China Stresses Fire Prevention At Heritage Sites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China's State Administration of
Cultural Heritage (SACH) has issued a circular requesting
localities to tighten fire safety measures at heritage sites
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The state's highest relics protection authorities urged local
administrations to strictly control combustible or explosive
substances near relic sites.
</P>
<P>
Relics experts suggest more precaution against fires during the
dry period of spring.  
</P>
