<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six Hospitalized After Gas Leak in SE Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Six men were hospitalized Friday
after being exposed to chlorine liquid gas at Matraville in the
south of Sydney in southeast Australia.
</P>
<P>
The gas leak resulted in the men complaining of varying degrees
of throat irritation and burning and breathing difficulties, local
government officials said.
</P>
<P>
One man also suffered chemical burns to his chest and left arm,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
It's believed the group were all in the same commercial
premises at the time of the leak. They were treated with oxygen
before being transported to the Prince of Wales Hospital.
</P>
<P>
All patients were in a stable condition, the officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
