<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia's Qantas Airline to Fly to E. Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Qantas airline will
begin regular flights to East Timor next month, the company
announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
Services between Darwin, in northern Australia, and Dili, in
East Timor, will operate four days a week from May 2, increasing
to twice daily from July 31, the airline said.
</P>
<P>
Qantas deputy Chief Executive Officer Geoff Dixon said the
services were in response to a growing demand from Australian
businesses seeking travel to East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Flying time is approximately one hour and 50 minutes, Qantas
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
