<HEADLINE> Palmeiras Beats El Nacional 4-1 in Copa Libertadores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- With two goals by striker Pena,
Brazil's Palmeiras whitewashed Ecuador's El Nacional 4-1 and
assumed the lead in Group 7 of the Copa Libertadores soccer
tournament in Sao Paulo on Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Palmeiras dominated El Nacional during the entire 90 minutes of
play with strong attacks and counterattacks that penetrated the
Ecuadorean defense.
</P>
