<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France's Pace Leads New Zealander in Congressional Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- France's Bertrand Pace leads
New Zealand's Dean Barker by one victory with one day left in the
Congressional Cup yachting race.
</P>
<P>
Pace, second in the International Sailing Federation's match-
race rankings, won three of four races Thursday in Long Beach
Harbour. Pace defeated top-rated Sten Mohr of Denmark by 10
seconds to retain first place with a 13-4 record.
</P>
<P>
Barker, a skipper for Team New Zealand during the America's Cup,
won all four of his races to hold second place at 12-5. Australia'
s Sebastien Destremau is third at 10-7.
</P>
<P>
Four skippers are tied for fourth place, the final cutoff point
for Friday's sailoff. Mohr, Australia's James Spithill, Germany's
Markus Wieser and Peter Holmberg from the U.S. Virgin Islands have
9-8 records.
</P>
<P>
The single-elimination sailoff will take place Friday after the

final set of round-robin matches. The first-place skipper will
sail against his fourth-place counterpart, and the second-place
and third-place entrants will face either other. The two winners
will meet for the championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
