<HEADLINE> Motor Sales in Czech Republic Record High in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Motor sales in the Czech Republic
hit a record high in the first quarter this year compared to the
same period last year, due in part to a recovering economy and
increasing consumer confidence, newspaper reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Compared to last year's figure, sales of cars surged 19 percent
this year during January to March to 37,000 units, Lubomir Tvardik,
executive president of the country's automakers' association, was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Domestic-made Skoda cars remained the best-selling brand in the
country, with sales reaching 18,000 units, followed by Volkswagen
with 2,300 units.
</P>
<P>
Tvardik credited the booming situation in the motor market to
economic recovery, which has considerably enhanced consumers'
confidence, and lower bank rates.
</P>
<P>
Consumers, buoyant at the economic revival, have reversed their
wait-and-see attitude and begun to spend lavishly, he said.
Meanwhile, he added, lower interest rates and the installment plan
widely used by car dealers have also lured consumers to spend.
</P>
</TEXT>
