<HEADLINE> Indonesian Badminton Team Counting on Hendrawan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Badminton
Association (PBSI) appears to suspect that Taufik Hidayat may be
under psychological pressure in the team's build up to the Thomas
Cup championship in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, next month.
</P>
<P>
"The worry stems from the fact that young Taufik, the team's
number one player, will be playing first," PBSI official M.F.
Siregar was quoted by the Indonesian Observer Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Siregar said that the team has taken an anticipatory move by
turning to Hendrawan, a more senior player, for hope. He added
that, despite being the second player, the association seems to be
counting on him yet again in the competition.
</P>
<P>
"Again, Hendrawan looks set to be the one most counted on,"
Siregar said.
</P>
<P>
The last time the two-yearly world men's team badminton event
took place in Hong Kong two years ago, Hendrawan played a pivotal
part in Indonesia's defeat of Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Hendrawan salvaged Indonesia's hopes by beating Yong Hock Kin
after Heryanto Arbi, who was expected to overcome Ong Ewe Hock in
the first single's match, was beaten instead.
</P>
<P>
At the recent Tokyo Open, Hendrawan proved he was a player to
be reckoned with when he edged out giant-killer Roslin Hasyim in
the semi-finals before losing to a Chinese player in the final.
</P>
<P>
"He will be our hope playing in the second singles (in Kuala
Lumpur)," Siregar said.
</P>
<P>
The team will be trying-out in Bogor, about 60 kilometers south
of Jakarta, on April 29, three days after the association is
expected to announce the team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
