<HEADLINE> China Steps Up Supervision Over Coalmine Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 14 (Xinhua) -The Hunan Provincial Coalmine
Safety Supervisory Bureau has been set up in Changsha, capital of
Hunan province this week.
</P>
<P>
Late last year, the State Council decided to reinforce safety
management in coal mines, by starting up a set of safety
supervisory organizations directly under the central authorities.
Safety supervisory offices will also be in place in different
large and medium-sized coalmines.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that 665 people were killed in
coalmine accidents in the first quarter of the year, 10 persons
more from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Establishment of the new coalmine safety supervisory bureaus in
16 provinces will be completed later this month, and coalmine
safety supervisory offices will go into operation as of the end of
June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
