<HEADLINE> COSCO to Open Three New Ocean-shipping Routes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The three new routes will be from Far East to Mediterranean,
from Far East to the east coast of the United States and from
Mediterranean to the east coast of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The three companies will pool 21 container ships with 2,000 to
3,500 TEUs (twenty-foot equivalent units) to engage in the service.
</P>
<P>
With the opening of the three new routes, COSCO's shipping
services will cover all the major ports around the Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the new routes will enhance COSCO's shipping
capacity from South China to South Asia and the east coast of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
COSCO has started cooperation with Kawasaki Kisen Kaisha Ltd.
and Yang Ming Lines since 1996. Now their cooperation involves 15
ocean-shipping routes and 92 liners, with the total shipping
capacity reaching 280,000 TEUs  
