<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Citizens Fond of Traveling: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- More and more Beijing citizens
are fond of traveling on holidays, according to a recent survey
issued by Beijing Municipal Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
The survey covering 1,112 households in China's capital showed
from the New Year Day of 1999 to the Spring Festival in 2000, 62
percent of citizens went on traveling with about 6.6 days on
average and daily spending of 252 yuan (30.4 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
This year, 58 percent of the citizens have travel plans. The
number of the citizens to make tour during the holidays at the
beginning of May is expected to increase 29.2 percent over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Traveling to overseas resorts also increased. At the Spring
Festival in 2000, four percent of travelers went abroad.
</P>
<P>
About 78 percent of travelers to overseas this year will join
travel groups organized by travel agencies.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that 68.8 percent of the travelers will
travel with their families. The rate will rise to 74.7 percent in
2001.  
</P>
</TEXT>
