<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0306 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pharm Industry Sets Target for 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's pharmaceutical
industry plans to generate a gross output value of 16.5 billion
yuan (about two billion US dollars) this year, up 14 percent over
last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the largest metropolis is set to realize a sales
revenue of 8.8 billion yuan and export 200 million US dollars
worth of goods.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of China's major drug producers.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Pharmaceutical (Group) Corporation, founded in
1996, is the largest of its kind in the country. It has 37 branch
companies, two listed companies, 45 Sino-foreign joint ventures
and a dozen scientific research centers and teaching institutions.
</P>
<P>
Of the joint ventures, 28 are involved in drug production and
18 in medical instruments and apparatuses.
</P>
<P>
Foreign partners of these joint ventures mainly come from the
United States, Germany, Switzerland, France, Norway, Italy, Japan,
the Republic of Korea and Finland. One third of the world's top 20
well-known pharmaceutical enterprises have set up joint ventures
in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The group exported 186 million US dollars worth of goods in
1999, an increase of 6.3 percent over 1999, and its joint ventures
exported 25.6 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai encourages overseas investment in the following areas:
</P>
<P>
-- Biotechnology drugs including genetic engineering drugs and
hepatitis B vaccine, monoclonal antibody drugs, polypeptide
synthetic drugs, enzymatic and genetic diagnose preparation,
cephalothin and new type antibiotics;
</P>
<P>
-- New synthetic drugs including all new synthetic drugs, new
synthetic technology; new drugs and preparations including control-
release and slow-release preparations, target and skin penetrating
drug preparations and fixed injections;
</P>
<P>
-- Natural drugs including the study of pharmacology about
active elements of natural resources chemicals, new type compound
drugs, oceanic resource drugs and new functional health food;
</P>
<P>
-- New types of pharmaceutical machinery including diagnosis,
treatment and monitoring apparatuses with the optical,
electromechanical and digital integration, flexible processing
technique, and intervening treatment machinery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
