<HEADLINE> Trade Between Fujian and Taiwan Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Taiwan and four
cities in Fujian Province, Xiamen, Zhangzhou, Quanzhou and Longyan,
reached 353 million US dollars during the first quarter of the
year, a 19.6 percent rise on a yearly basis, according to Xiamen
Customs.
</P>
<P>
The total include 54 million US dollars of exports to Taiwan,
up 32.5 percent, and 298 million US dollars of imports from Taiwan,
up 17.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises in the four cities accounted for 86.
2 percent of total imports from Taiwan and 63 percent of exports
to Taiwan. 
</P>
