<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Expels Italian Mafia Kingpin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An Italian mafia kingpin has
been detained in Mexico and expelled to Italy, the Federal
Attorney Office (PGR) said Thursday in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Giuseppe Montanti, a Sicilian mafia head and leader of the "
Stidda" (Star) criminal ring which operates mainly in Italy's
Agrigento and Sicilia, is considered one of the most dangerous
Mafiosi in the world.
</P>
<P>
Montanti, 44, was arrested by Mexican Federal Judicial Police (
PJF) agents on Wednesday in the Mexican tourist city of Acapulco,
where he had been living illegally for more than six years, said
the PGR.
</P>
<P>
He was put under the custody of the Mexican National Migration
Institute, since he violated the Mexican General Law of Population,
and he was expelled to Italy.
</P>
<P>
The arrest was the culmination of several months of
investigation by the PJF in collaboration with agents from Germany
and Italy.
</P>
<P>
Montanti had destroyed all his identity documents to escape
prosecution, but the Interpol in Rome obtained his fingerprints
and photographs.
</P>
<P>
A PGR spokesman confirmed that Montanti escaped from Italy in
1994. He was charged with killing Italian judge Rosario Livantino
in 1990 and other crimes. The Italian police has issued five
arrest warrants, four of them for the killings of policemen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
