<DOCNO> XIE20000414.0317 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Party Wins Majority in S. Korean Parliamentary Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Both ruling Millennium Democratic
Party (MDP) and opposition Grand National Party (GNP) failed to
claim a needed majority in Thursday's South Korean parliamentary
elections.
</P>
<P>
The results of the elections released by the National Election
Commission showed that the GNP has won 133 of the 273 seats in the
National Assembly, while President Kim Dae-jung's MDP came in the
second place with 115 seats.
</P>
<P>
United Liberal Democrats (ULD) won 17 seats and the Democratic
People's Party (DPP) one, New Korea Party of Hope one, and other
parties and independents eight.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's election clearly outlined a virtual two-party system
with the MDP lagging 18 seats behind the GNP which remains the
largest party in the unicameral parliament and ULD will be out of
the parliamentary picture as it is unable to get 20 seats legally
required to form a floor negotiation group.
</P>
<P>
The election features growing public discontent and cynicism
toward politics as voter turnout reached a mere 57.2 percent,
below 60 percent for the first time in the country's general
election history, analysts say.
</P>
<P>
Support rate for GNP stood at 39 percent, followed by MDP with
35.9 percent, ULD 9.8 percent, and DPP 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The result also proved deeply-rooted regional antagonism in the
nation. GNP swept its stronghold of North Kyongsang and South
Kyongsang provinces while MDP won all seats in its political base
North Cholla and South Cholla provinces.
</P>
<P>
The MDP's strong showing was a result of its dominance in Seoul,
along with better-than-expected results in Cheju Island, Kangwon
and Chungchong provinces.
</P>
<P>
However, its failure to snatch the largest party position in
parliament is expected to remain a heavy political obstacle in the
process of President Kim's political and economic reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
