<HEADLINE> Stowaway-detection Succeeds: Albania and Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The allied marine patrol of
Albania and Italy fulfilled its largest mission this year by
catching 320 Albanian stowaways on 13 yachts, an Albanian police
official said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Perparim Muho with the Vlora Police Office revealed that the
mission was carried out on the sea between Vlora and Italy's
Otranto Straits Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
All the stowaways, who were mostly Albanian and Moldovan women
bound for Italy to work as prostitutes, were shipped back to
Albania.
</P>
<P>
Some 37 other stowaways boarding their ships were also spotted
in Vlora, according to the police.
</P>
<P>
The allied patrol has succeeded in detecting over 200 ships and
more than 3,800 stowaways this year. 
