<HEADLINE> Facilities for Disabled Set Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China's largest industrial and
commercial city of Shanghai has constructed special lanes for the
wheel-chaired confined people and the blind, China Daily reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The move was part of the efforts to welcome the Fifth National
Games of the Disabled, which is to be held next month in the city.
</P>
<P>
The special lanes in underground tunnels, hotels, shopping
malls and roads were built mainly in the 11 districts where
various competitions will be held.
</P>
<P>
More facilities for the disabled will also be constructed in
areas other than those near stadiums for the games, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
To abide by Chinese laws to protect the disabled, many new
buildings have planned or constructed special lanes and other
facilities, such as special toilets for the disabled. 
