Department under the Information Industry Ministry (IIM),
described the IT development as China's pillar and strategic
economic sector which should be given top priority to.
</P>
<P>
"The mainland has the advantage of talent and the market,
Taiwan has technological edge, and the cooperation between the two
sides will benefit both sides," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang was optimistic about the prospects of the business, which
has had a 20-year history of cooperation, citing the fact that the
two sides have jointly set up a Chinese character bank for
computer processing of Chinese words. 
