Standing Committee of the People's Congress of Xinyang, a city in
central Henan Province, has been removed from his post for
violating Party discipline and law.
</P>
<P>
Jing has also been expelled from the Party with the approval of
the Henan Provincial Committee of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
He Guangcai, deputy secretary of Henan Provincial Party
Commission For Discipline Inspection, made the announcement at a
press conference Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During his term as Chairman of the local legislative body, Jing
made abuse of his power to seek personal profit and even went so
far as to distribute among a small group financial fund set aside
by the government.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he attempted to undermine the investigation of the
case by fabricating evidences and asking his colleagues to provide
false testimony about his involvement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
