WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Justice Department announced Thursday
that it has agreed to delay any enforcement action to take six-
year-old Cuban shipwreck survivor, Elian Gonzalez, from his Miami
relatives who defied a government deadline to return the boy to
his father.
</P>
<P>
