<HEADLINE> Best Released from Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Soccer legend George Best was
allowed home on Thursday after spending five weeks battling an
alcohol-related liver problem in a private hospital.
</P>
<P>
The 53-year-old was first admitted to Cromwell Hospital in
Kensington on 8 March, complaining of severe stomach pains.
</P>
<P>
His consultant at the London hospital, Professor Roger Williams,
said "Mr Best has improved considerably this week and has been
allowed to go home today to continue convalescing."
</P>
<P>
He added that the ex-soccer star would receive weekly checks,
but it may be some time before he feels completely well.
</P>
<P>
The former Manchester United and Northern Ireland player has
always had a reputation as a heavy drinker.
</P>
<P>
He recently gave his 27-year-old wife Alex a pledge that he
would stop drinking for good. 
</P>
