<HEADLINE> Third World Countries Call WTO Paying Attention of Them </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Third World Countries attending
the South Summit here asked on Friday in the final declaration the
World Trade Organization (WTO)to pay more attention to need of
them.
</P>
<P>
They advocate the restoration of confidence in the multilateral
trade system, which should contribute to the economic growth and
development of the countries of the South. It was expressed in the
final Declaration of the South Summit to be passed late today, the
final day of the Summit being held here.
</P>
<P>
They insist on the need for the developed countries to fulfill
their commitments to fully and immediately implement the provision
of special and differential treatment for the products and
services exported by the developing countries, for the
strengthening of the system of trade preferences, considering
their problems of vulnerability and the risk of marginalization in
the global economy.
</P>
<P>
They also complained that the liberalization of international
trade and the WTO have not provided the benefits expected by the
developing countries and have not led to their full participation
in the multilateral trading system, demanding the implementation
of the Uruguay Round Agreement in accordance to its letter and
spirit.
</P>
<P>
The leaders condemned the discrimination to the use of trade
remedies for protectionist purposes, through antidumping actions,
while countervailing duties and safeguard measure are increasing,
according to the document. 
</P>
</TEXT>
