<HEADLINE> Continuity IRA Admits Failed Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Continuity IRA (Irish
Republican Army) said Friday that it was behind Thursday's failed
mortar bomb attack on a police station in Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The dissident republican group, made up from breakaway members
of the IRA opposed to the Good Friday Agreement peace accord, has
carried out a number of attacks recently.
</P>
<P>
No-one was injured in the latest incident in which a device
exploded in a car left outside Rosslea Royal Ulster Constabulary(
RUC) Station near the border in County Fermanagh at midnight on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police sources told the BBC that republican dissidents are
actively recruiting along the border and in other areas of
Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Dissident republican groups, opposed to the current peace
process, are almost certainly planning further attacks on security
and commercial targets, the sources added. 
