<HEADLINE> South Countries Ask to Reduce Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They expressed concern over the persistence of the external
debt problem in the South, where the vicious cycle of debt and
underdevelopment has become even further entrenched.
</P>
<P>
They are alarmed at the fact that debt servicing has grown at a
much greater rate than the debt itself, and the burden of debt
payments have become heavier in many countries of the South,
including countries with low and middle incomes.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the Group of 77 (G-77) attended the South Summit
from April 12 to 14 in the capital city of Havana.
</P>
<P>
This is the first ever summit of the organization since its
founding in 1964. The group has grown to a group of 133,
