<HEADLINE> U.S. Imposes Sanctions on DPRK, Iran Entities for Alleged Proliferation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States, once again
brandishing the punitive baton, said on Friday that it imposed
sanctions on five "entities" in Iran and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) for alleged missile proliferation.
</P>
<P>
"We have imposed penalties on North Korean and Iranian entities
for knowingly engaging in missile technology transfers," State
Department spokesman James Rubin said at a briefing.
</P>
